Docker images and continer
******************************************
images
******************************************
serach the image in local machine
    
    command : docker search image-name

    example : docker search almalinux

docker pull means(download the image):pull the image from docker hub to local machine
  
  command :docker pull image-name

   example:docker pull almalinux

check the image is download or not

    command :docker images

**********************************************
continer
**********************************************
There are two ways to create a continer 
  1.attached mode
  2.dettached mode

1.attached mode:In attached mode the continer is create and moving the inside the continer
   command:docker run -it image-name /bin/bash

   example:docker run -it almalinux /bin/bash

2.dettached mode:Here the continer is create and exit (ouside the continer) 
   command:docker run -itd image-name /bin/bash

   example:docker run -itd almalinux /bin/bash

******************************
continer stages
******************************
There are three continer stages :
 1.Running state
 2.Paused state
 3.Exited state

>Check the continer status
       
       command :docker ps
Here show the running continer

>Check the how many continer in docker 

       command :docker ps -a
Here the command shows the all stages continer

1.Running state :if the continer is created automatically the continer is go to running state,the continer is not running then start the continer by using this command

   command:docker start continer-id

   example :docker start 7981961842123
 Here the start only one continer by using above command
    
    command:docker start $ (docker ps -a) 
 Here the start the all continer at a time

2.a.Paused state :docker pause command is suspend(freeze) the all running continer

for single continer:

  command : docker pause continer-id

  example:docker pause q3 (continer id is unique here we take either first two letters or first three letters)

check the status (docker ps)

for mutiple continers

  command:docker unpause $(docker ps -a)

 b. unpaused state :docker unpause command is used to contineres paused state to running state

for single continer:

    command:docker unpause continer-id

    example:docker unpause w3

for multiple continers:

    command :docker unpause continer-id
 
    example:docker unpause $(docker ps -a) 

3.Exited stage:Stop the running continer

for single continer:

    command :docker stop continer-id

    example:docker stop r1

for multiple commands:
 
    command:docker stop $(docker ps -a)

